From 32e000c8478f828631631589b71ac768d317225b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 22:46:22 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 42/48] Add rich items + fuzzy search to warp.ui.showPalette
 (oh-my-warp)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The picker now feels like the native command palette instead of a stack of
plain buttons:

  - Search input at the top with built-in fuzzy matching against both label
    and description (label matches outrank description-only hits).
  - Keyboard navigation: up/down to move selection, enter to accept, ESC to
    close (via the parent Modal's existing binding). The search editor uses
    PropagateAndNoOpNavigationKeys::Always so navigation keys reach us as
    EditorEvent::Navigate / Enter.
  - Per-row hover and selected backgrounds (theme.surface_2 / surface_overlay_1).
  - Click-to-pick still works; hovering a row also moves the selection so
    keyboard and mouse paths agree.

PalettePluginItem grows three optional fields:

  - icon:        sigil/emoji rendered in a fixed-width left column
  - description: dimmed inline subtitle under the label
  - kbd:         monospace keystroke chip on the right edge

JS schema is now [{ label, command, icon?, description?, kbd? }] (back-compat:
the old { label, command } still works).

The accept path is unchanged: the body emits PluginPaletteEvent::Selected(id)
and Workspace runs it as a fresh RunPluginCommand — so we still never re-enter
plugin.get_mut() from inside the calling callback.
